WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:06.440
‐ I'm not a monster, Jake.
[chuckles] Hi, I'm Chucky,

00:06.440 --> 00:08.675
and I'm your friend
till the end.

00:08.675 --> 00:12.045
‐ Caroline, would you maybe
like to meet Chucky sometime?

00:12.045 --> 00:15.115
‐ What if he doesn't like me?
‐ I'm Detective Evans.

00:15.115 --> 00:16.116
Do you know
that there was a break‐in

00:16.116 --> 00:17.251
at the school last night?

00:17.251 --> 00:19.486
The only thing missing
was a doll.

00:19.486 --> 00:21.688
‐ I'm sorry,
I‐‐I shouldn't have lied.

00:21.688 --> 00:23.490
I've never done anything
like that before.

00:23.490 --> 00:26.426
‐ Your sister adores you.
‐ She barely knows I exist.

00:26.426 --> 00:28.362
She doesn't even like
to be touched.

00:28.362 --> 00:30.497
‐ Where is he?
Did Junior take him?

00:30.497 --> 00:34.168
‐ What are you talking about?
‐ Chucky. He's gone.

00:34.168 --> 00:37.337
‐ Hi, I'm Chucky.
I'm looking for a party.

00:37.337 --> 00:38.605
‐ I‐‐I've gone to find Lexy.

00:38.605 --> 00:40.274
I just, I‐‐I need
to make sure she's okay.

00:40.274 --> 00:44.278
‐ Seven minutes in hell!
[crowd cheers] ‐ Where's Lexy?

00:44.278 --> 00:46.680
‐ Probably kissing Junior
somewhere.

00:46.680 --> 00:50.350
‐ Well, at least she's gonna
die doin' what she loves.

00:50.350 --> 00:52.186
[knife slashes]
[sudden musical flourish]

00:52.186 --> 00:55.689
‐ Leave my friends alone!

00:55.689 --> 00:58.225
‐ You have a serious
doll problem. ‐ If you only knew.

00:58.225 --> 01:01.328
[crowd chanting, cheering]

01:01.361 --> 01:03.263
[ominous music]

01:03.297 --> 01:06.300
[laughter]

01:06.333 --> 01:07.534
♪ ♪

01:07.568 --> 01:09.002
[electricity zapping]
‐ Some people just

01:09.002 --> 01:10.804
deserve to die.

01:10.804 --> 01:12.573
‐ I‐‐I can't let her
get away with this.

01:12.573 --> 01:15.042
‐ Kill the bitch
before she kills you.

01:15.042 --> 01:16.677
You know you want to.

01:16.677 --> 01:21.448
♪ ♪

01:22.683 --> 01:25.118
[owl hooting]

01:25.152 --> 01:27.754
[eerie music]

01:27.754 --> 01:31.658
‐ So, Jake, are you more
of a stabbing kind of guy

01:31.658 --> 01:33.627
or a strangulation kind of guy?

01:33.627 --> 01:40.667
'Cause I see the appeal
of both. ‐ I‐‐I don't know.

01:40.667 --> 01:42.035
Neither.

01:42.035 --> 01:44.037
I‐‐I don't know
if I can do this.

01:44.037 --> 01:47.774
‐ Oh, sure you can.
Easy.

01:47.774 --> 01:49.676
You want hard?
[chuckles]

01:49.676 --> 01:54.047
Try choking someone with these.

01:54.047 --> 01:57.217
You hate her, don't you?
‐ Of course I hate her.

01:57.217 --> 02:00.254
‐ She's definitely
got it comin'.

02:00.254 --> 02:02.689
‐ Yeah, and‐‐
and I want her dead.

02:02.689 --> 02:05.159
But what if I'm not a killer?

02:05.159 --> 02:09.296
‐ Everybody's a killer
if you push 'em far enough.

02:09.296 --> 02:15.435
And I think Lexy's pushed you
right over the edge.

02:15.435 --> 02:22.042
‐ Chucky?

02:22.042 --> 02:26.213
How did you end up like this?
‐ Great question.

02:26.213 --> 02:30.484
In a lot of ways, it was your
standard voodoo soul transfer.

02:30.484 --> 02:34.221
My big innovation
was using the doll.

02:34.221 --> 02:37.090
You see‐‐
‐ No, I mean,

02:37.090 --> 02:41.795
when did you become a killer
in the first place? ‐ Oh.

02:41.795 --> 02:43.764
[chuckles]
Oh, I get it.

02:43.764 --> 02:46.567
All right, kid,
let me tell you the story

02:46.567 --> 02:53.540
of my first time.
You never forget your first.

02:53.540 --> 02:55.442
[creepy laughter]

02:55.442 --> 02:59.379
Step one, picking your prey.

02:59.379 --> 03:02.516
Could be a total stranger.
Could be someone close to you.

03:02.516 --> 03:04.218
‐ I want cake now!

03:04.218 --> 03:06.386
Charles, hurry up
and cut the cake!

03:06.386 --> 03:10.290
‐ Or maybe someone you just
want to shut the fuck up.

03:10.290 --> 03:12.159
But no matter
how you slice it,

03:12.159 --> 03:15.095
you got to find
that special someone.

03:15.095 --> 03:17.297
‐ ♪ Everybody wants
to be different ♪

03:17.297 --> 03:20.100
‐ ♪ Just be you ♪
‐ ♪ I know it's true ♪

03:20.100 --> 03:21.435
‐ ♪ Just be you ♪

03:21.435 --> 03:25.439
‐ ♪ But, baby,
please don't change ♪

03:25.439 --> 03:28.175
♪ Just be you ♪

03:28.175 --> 03:31.345
‐ ♪ Don't you do it,
please be true ♪

03:31.345 --> 03:35.148
♪ 'Cause you're mine,
just be you ♪

03:35.148 --> 03:38.218
‐ ♪ Don't look
through everybody ♪

03:38.218 --> 03:41.655
[ringing crescendos
over music]

03:41.688 --> 03:44.358
[cheers]
‐ [grunting]

03:44.391 --> 03:45.592
[music fades]

03:45.592 --> 03:48.428
‐ A mass murderer continued
his reign of terror today,

03:48.428 --> 03:50.497
leaving two more dead
in his wake.

03:50.497 --> 03:52.499
As violent crimes
continue to rise,

03:52.499 --> 03:54.668
we urge all citizens
of Hackensack

03:54.668 --> 03:56.403
not to go out alone at night.

03:56.403 --> 03:57.304
[knife whooshes]

03:57.337 --> 03:58.739
[playful '60s music returns]

03:58.772 --> 04:01.642
[people cheering,
noisemakers tooting]

04:01.675 --> 04:04.645
[playful spooky music]

04:04.678 --> 04:11.718
♪ ♪

04:20.527 --> 04:23.430
[school bell rings]

04:24.231 --> 04:27.267
[students chattering
indistinctly]

04:36.577 --> 04:40.414
‐ Kim, you here for Devon?
I don't have him till fifth.

04:40.414 --> 04:45.085
‐ No, actually I'm‐‐I'm here
officially, Ms. Fairchild.

04:45.085 --> 04:46.420
‐ Oh.
‐ I'd like to talk

04:46.420 --> 04:49.256
about Jake Wheeler.

04:49.256 --> 04:51.658
‐ Well, I'm sorry,
but I'm not really comfortable

04:51.658 --> 04:53.527
talking about my students,

04:53.527 --> 04:56.797
especially one that's been
through what Jake has recently,

04:56.797 --> 04:58.632
Detective Evans.

04:58.632 --> 05:01.635
‐ Look, I appreciate
your concern for these kids.

05:01.635 --> 05:03.670
It's my job
to be concerned too.

05:03.670 --> 05:06.306
But not just for them,
for everyone in the community.

05:06.306 --> 05:08.208
‐ Great, then you understand
my position.

05:08.208 --> 05:12.179
‐ What I understand is
everywhere Jake Wheeler goes,

05:12.179 --> 05:14.181
death seems to follow.

05:14.181 --> 05:16.683
Now maybe his father
and housekeeper

05:16.683 --> 05:18.218
were just accidents,

05:18.218 --> 05:20.354
but I think Jake knows more
than he's saying.

05:20.354 --> 05:22.356
‐ I'm sorry,
but are you suggesting‐‐

05:22.356 --> 05:23.624
‐ And if he does
know something,

05:23.624 --> 05:30.664
who's to say one of these kids
won't be the next to be hurt?

05:30.664 --> 05:32.099
‐ I'm sorry.
I can't help you.

05:32.099 --> 05:37.171
‐ Can't or won't? ‐ [sighs]

05:45.579 --> 05:48.182
[school bell rings]

05:48.215 --> 05:51.185
[students chattering
indistinctly]

05:56.256 --> 06:00.194
[soft ominous music]

06:00.194 --> 06:02.029
‐ [sighs]

06:02.029 --> 06:08.035
♪ ♪

06:08.035 --> 06:12.606
Oh, um...
‐ Am I too late to say "boo"?

06:12.606 --> 06:16.076
‐ I'll allow it.
‐ Hey, you doing okay?

06:16.076 --> 06:18.378
‐ Yeah, I'm totally fine.
It's‐‐it's no big deal.

06:18.378 --> 06:19.546
‐ Well, I think
it's a big deal.

06:19.546 --> 06:22.683
I mean, what Lexy did to you,
that was cruel and disgusting.

06:22.683 --> 06:24.218
I'm sorry you had to see that.

06:24.218 --> 06:26.820
I can't imagine
how much that hurt.

06:26.820 --> 06:29.156
‐ Well, thanks.

06:29.156 --> 06:32.092
‐ I wish I could like‐‐
[sighs]

06:32.092 --> 06:34.094
Never mind.
No, it's stupid, no.

06:34.094 --> 06:35.295
‐ No, tell me.

06:35.295 --> 06:38.031
‐ [sighs]
Well, I wish I could, like,

06:38.031 --> 06:42.169
protect you or something.
‐ [laughs lightly]

06:42.169 --> 06:45.672
I mean, I guess
it does hurt a little.

06:45.672 --> 06:48.041
[tender music]

06:48.041 --> 06:50.110
‐ I still can't believe
she did that.

06:50.110 --> 06:53.113
You must have been so angry.

06:53.113 --> 06:54.715
‐ Well, I mean,
of course, I was angry.

06:54.715 --> 06:56.483
You know,
Lexy can be a real bitch.

06:56.483 --> 06:59.486
You know what she's like.

06:59.486 --> 07:01.355
I mean, no, no, no,
we're cool now.

07:01.355 --> 07:04.124
It's‐‐no, but she was
just messing around.

07:04.124 --> 07:06.059
[sighs]
[phone buzzes]

07:06.059 --> 07:08.562
Oh.
[phone buzzes longer]

07:08.562 --> 07:11.064
[phone chimes]
Oh, um,

07:11.064 --> 07:15.402
I got to go do a project‐‐
homework, and‐‐

07:15.402 --> 07:18.038
I‐‐I got to go.
‐ Uh, see you later?

07:18.038 --> 07:21.675
‐ I don't know.
Uh, I mean, maybe.

07:21.675 --> 07:25.612
See you, Devon.

07:25.612 --> 07:28.582
[eerie music]

07:28.615 --> 07:30.450
♪ ♪

07:30.484 --> 07:32.352
[crows cawing]

07:32.386 --> 07:34.087
[phone chimes]

07:34.087 --> 07:39.126
‐ Jake, perfect.
We need to chat.

07:39.126 --> 07:41.161
‐ Uh‐‐
I mean, I'm‐‐

07:41.161 --> 07:43.530
I'm meeting some friends
and I'm kind of late.

07:43.530 --> 07:44.398
‐ It'll just take a minute.

07:44.398 --> 07:46.066
I just wanted you
to hear it from me.

07:46.066 --> 07:47.401
I've asked your aunt and uncle

07:47.401 --> 07:50.404
to come in for a meeting
with me tonight.

07:50.404 --> 07:52.806
‐ What, why?
Did I do something wrong?

07:52.806 --> 07:54.408
‐ No, no, no, no, Jake,
you haven't.

07:54.408 --> 07:56.476
I'm also inviting
Lexy's parents.

07:56.476 --> 07:57.611
I think this whole thing

07:57.611 --> 08:00.113
between the two of you has
gotten a little out of hand,

08:00.113 --> 08:02.349
and I think getting
the parents‐‐um, I'm sorry,

08:02.349 --> 08:04.218
the‐‐the guardians
together will help

08:04.218 --> 08:07.120
to diffuse the situation.
‐ You don't have to do that.

08:07.120 --> 08:08.222
You know, me and Lexy are
really cool now.

08:08.222 --> 08:10.357
It's‐‐
it's all good.

08:10.357 --> 08:12.626
‐ I saw the pictures
from Oliver's party.

08:12.626 --> 08:16.430
They're all over school.

08:16.430 --> 08:18.298
‐ [sighs]
‐ You don't need to pretend

08:18.298 --> 08:21.502
like everything's fine, Jake.

08:21.502 --> 08:24.371
[phone chimes]
‐ Um‐‐

08:24.371 --> 08:28.041
you know what,
this whole parent‐‐

08:28.041 --> 08:30.777
guardian meetup thing,
it's‐‐it's‐‐it's great.

08:30.777 --> 08:32.613
Yeah, it's a really good idea.

08:32.613 --> 08:34.314
Yeah, um‐‐
‐ Okay.

08:34.314 --> 08:37.084
[phone chimes]
‐ Um, yeah, see you later.

08:37.084 --> 08:39.486
‐ Uh, listen.

08:39.486 --> 08:40.787
[phone chimes]

08:40.787 --> 08:43.123
I want you to know
that if you're ever

08:43.123 --> 08:46.226
in any sort of trouble,
I just want you to know

08:46.226 --> 08:50.564
that you can always come to me,
yeah? You can trust me.

08:50.564 --> 08:53.133
[tender music]

08:53.133 --> 08:55.636
‐ Thanks, Miss F.
‐ Okay.

08:55.636 --> 08:57.704
[phone chimes twice]

08:59.273 --> 09:01.141
[sighs]

09:01.175 --> 09:04.211
[phone chimes repeatedly]

09:05.479 --> 09:08.682
[creepy music]

09:08.715 --> 09:11.084
♪ ♪

09:11.084 --> 09:12.619
‐ The next thing you got to do

09:12.619 --> 09:15.656
is really get to know
your victim.

09:15.656 --> 09:22.563
What they like, where they go.

09:22.563 --> 09:27.568
But eventually, you got
to get your victim alone.

09:27.568 --> 09:29.436
[phone chimes]

09:29.436 --> 09:36.677
Keep it intimate.
Really set the mood.

09:36.677 --> 09:38.779
Timing is everything.

09:38.779 --> 09:44.484
You're looking for that magic
moment, just the two of you.

09:44.484 --> 09:45.786
[phone chimes]

09:45.819 --> 09:48.755
[suspenseful music]

09:48.789 --> 09:52.392
♪ ♪

09:52.426 --> 09:54.061
[phone chimes]

09:54.061 --> 10:01.768
‐ [breathing heavily]

10:01.768 --> 10:03.570
‐ [panting]

10:03.570 --> 10:06.507
[heartbeat thumping]

10:14.715 --> 10:22.489
‐ [panting]

10:22.489 --> 10:25.359
[bird calls]

10:27.661 --> 10:30.364
[frantic music]

10:30.397 --> 10:32.399
♪ ♪

10:32.399 --> 10:40.307
‐ Whoa! The hell are you doing?

10:40.307 --> 10:42.042
‐ I‐‐I wasn't doing anything.
I was‐‐

10:42.042 --> 10:45.045
I was‐‐
‐ What's your problem?

10:45.045 --> 10:51.118
Why the hell are you
following me? Whatever, creep.

10:57.524 --> 11:00.294
‐ The moment
isn't always right,

11:00.294 --> 11:06.166
but I promise you,
the right moment always comes.

11:16.176 --> 11:19.146
[birds calling]
‐ [panting]

11:31.058 --> 11:35.329
Hey, babe.
Oh, thanks for grabbing it.

11:35.329 --> 11:40.100
How'd you like my playlist?

11:40.100 --> 11:43.370
Jeez, moody much?
What's your problem?

11:43.370 --> 11:45.772
‐ It's Jake.
‐ Oh, God.

11:45.772 --> 11:48.175
‐ You really went
too far this time.

11:48.175 --> 11:50.110
‐ It was funny.
It got like, 400 likes.

11:50.110 --> 11:54.615
‐ You dressed up
as his dead dad‐‐ my uncle.

11:54.615 --> 11:56.750
‐ Hold your breath
for my apology.

11:56.750 --> 12:00.387
‐ It was fucked up, Lex.
You crossed a line.

12:00.387 --> 12:03.257
And now‐‐
‐ And now?

12:03.257 --> 12:04.725
What?
‐ [sighs]

12:04.725 --> 12:06.360
You need to apologize to Jake.

12:06.360 --> 12:09.496
‐ [laughs]
Also fucking no way.

12:09.496 --> 12:11.131
Never.
‐ I'm serious.

12:11.131 --> 12:13.634
You need to talk to him.
‐ Yeah?

12:13.634 --> 12:18.639
And what if I don't?
What's Jake gonna do?

12:18.639 --> 12:20.774
‐ Honestly...

12:20.774 --> 12:23.577
[sighs]
I don't know.

12:23.577 --> 12:28.348
Look, I'll talk to you later,
okay?

12:28.348 --> 12:31.318
[tense music]

12:31.351 --> 12:37.624
♪ ♪

12:37.624 --> 12:40.327
‐ No.

12:40.327 --> 12:41.762
‐ [sighs]
Sweetie, come on.

12:41.762 --> 12:45.732
‐ No.
‐ Come on. ‐ [screams]

12:45.732 --> 12:49.503
‐ Oh, my God,
why is she acting like this?

12:49.503 --> 12:51.038
‐ [shushing]
‐ No.

12:51.038 --> 12:53.140
‐ She likes her blankie.
‐ No.

12:53.140 --> 12:55.042
‐ Mom, the sunglasses
or the blankie.

12:55.042 --> 12:57.177
‐ No!
‐ What about her sunglasses?

12:57.177 --> 12:59.479
‐ I looked in the drawer,
Nathan, they're not there.

12:59.479 --> 13:01.315
[sighs]
Why does she always do this

13:01.315 --> 13:02.516
when I'm heading out the door?

13:02.516 --> 13:04.384
‐ No. No.
‐ Sweetie, it's okay.

13:04.384 --> 13:05.752
‐ No.
No.

13:05.752 --> 13:07.387
‐ It's all right, you're okay.

13:07.387 --> 13:09.590
Look, look, look, look.
‐ No.

13:09.590 --> 13:11.625
[groaning]
‐ Here.

13:11.625 --> 13:12.759
‐ No.
‐ Here, hey.

13:12.759 --> 13:14.595
‐ No.
‐ Hey, what can I get you?

13:14.595 --> 13:18.599
‐ I want Chucky.
Chucky is my best friend!

13:18.599 --> 13:22.236
I want Chucky!
I want Chucky!

13:22.236 --> 13:25.205
[creepy music]

13:25.239 --> 13:26.340
♪ ♪

13:26.373 --> 13:29.309
[ominous music]

13:29.343 --> 13:36.450
♪ ♪

13:57.638 --> 14:00.641
‐ [grunting]

14:08.715 --> 14:16.056
‐ Hey, freak show.
Whoa, that looks sharp.

14:16.056 --> 14:23.630
‐ Junior's not home.
‐ Who cares? I'm here for you.

14:23.630 --> 14:29.503
What's that for anyway?
‐ It's for gardening.

14:29.503 --> 14:31.171
Actually,
for my new sculpture house‐‐

14:31.171 --> 14:33.040
‐ Whatever, don't care.

14:33.040 --> 14:34.741
[building suspenseful music]

14:34.741 --> 14:38.212
You know, Dad took us
to a wax museum once.

14:38.212 --> 14:40.547
Totally sucked.

14:40.547 --> 14:45.219
But they had this
"Chamber of Terror,"

14:45.219 --> 14:49.122
torture stuff.
‐ [breathing shakily]

14:49.122 --> 14:51.725
‐ All these insane tools
on a wall just like this one.

14:51.725 --> 14:53.327
It was actually pretty cool.

14:53.327 --> 14:54.561
[music ends abruptly]

14:54.561 --> 14:59.500
You look even weirder
than usual right now.

14:59.500 --> 15:01.101
‐ W‐‐Why are you even here?

15:01.101 --> 15:02.703
‐ I'm here because
I need to talk to you,

15:02.703 --> 15:07.541
if you can fit me into
your busy gardening schedule.

15:07.541 --> 15:11.578
‐ Okay, talk.

15:11.578 --> 15:17.184
‐ I want to...apologize

15:17.184 --> 15:24.091
for the whole dead dad
Halloween costume thing.

15:24.091 --> 15:27.327
I guess I can sort of see why
you'd take that the wrong way.

15:27.327 --> 15:29.596
‐ There was a right way?

15:29.596 --> 15:33.767
‐ [sighs]
All right, okay, um...

15:33.767 --> 15:39.173
Sometimes when I'm upset, I...

15:39.173 --> 15:42.676
hurt people or something.

15:42.676 --> 15:50.384
And it‐‐
[sighs] Look, I'm sorry

15:50.384 --> 15:58.025
I hurt your feelings. I am.

15:58.025 --> 16:00.360
Even though you're like a weird
social tumor who's creepy AF

16:00.360 --> 16:03.096
and you thought you could mess
with me at the talent show.

16:03.096 --> 16:05.165
[tense music]

16:05.165 --> 16:08.535
I just thought since
maybe I was a little harsh,

16:08.535 --> 16:10.504
I should be the bigger man.

16:10.504 --> 16:15.309
You know, I think people really
underestimate my humility.

16:15.309 --> 16:17.010
[laughs lightly]
Anyway,

16:17.010 --> 16:20.581
now that I've done this,
like, act of charity,

16:20.581 --> 16:23.784
I'm sure you want to know
what you can do for me.

16:23.784 --> 16:27.521
‐ Wasn't really thinking that,
but, uh,

16:27.521 --> 16:31.225
hey, Lexy,
what could I do for you?

16:31.225 --> 16:34.127
‐ Chucky.
‐ Chucky?

16:34.127 --> 16:37.498
‐ Yeah.
Can I, like, have him?

16:37.498 --> 16:39.766
Not for me.
I think he's totally creepy.

16:39.766 --> 16:44.571
For Caroline.
‐ N‐no, no, absolutely not. No.

16:44.571 --> 16:47.241
‐ Excuse me?
‐ You can't have him

16:47.241 --> 16:50.377
for any reason.
You‐‐you can never have him.

16:50.377 --> 16:53.547
‐ You mean, I came all the way
here to apologize,

16:53.547 --> 16:57.351
and this is how you repay me?
‐ Yeah, that's exactly how.

16:57.351 --> 17:03.190
‐ [sighs]
You are a waste!

17:03.190 --> 17:06.226
[scoffs]
Ugh!

17:06.260 --> 17:09.329
[intense, dark music]

17:09.363 --> 17:12.065
♪ ♪

17:12.065 --> 17:16.303
‐ So you had the chance
to kill her and you choked.

17:16.303 --> 17:23.744
And not in the good way.

17:23.744 --> 17:27.047
[music intensifies]

17:27.080 --> 17:34.021
♪ ♪

17:34.021 --> 17:38.625
It's called
"completion anxiety."

17:38.625 --> 17:40.093
‐ [sighs]
Look, I wanted to do it.

17:40.093 --> 17:43.730
I just couldn't.

17:43.730 --> 17:47.234
And besides,
with my dad and Annie, I...

17:47.234 --> 17:50.771
couldn't just kill Lexy
in the garage. It's too risky.

17:50.771 --> 17:57.377
‐ Pussy.
And that means once again,

17:57.377 --> 18:02.082
I got to do your dirty work
for you. ‐ I‐‐I don't know.

18:02.082 --> 18:05.519
‐ Oh, come on, Jake.
Let me fix your Lexy problem.

18:05.519 --> 18:08.589
‐ How?

18:08.589 --> 18:13.227
‐ We give her what she wants.
[chuckles]

18:13.227 --> 18:20.167
♪ ♪

18:20.167 --> 18:25.038
Shiny.

18:25.038 --> 18:30.644
Mm‐hmm.

18:30.644 --> 18:33.580
[suspenseful music]

18:33.614 --> 18:40.554
♪ ♪

18:40.587 --> 18:43.090
[audio rewinding]

18:43.090 --> 18:46.059
‐ You know,
Lexy can be a real bitch.

18:46.059 --> 18:47.728
I mean, no, no, no,
we're cool now.

18:47.728 --> 18:52.099
It's‐‐no, she was
just messing around.

18:52.099 --> 18:54.234
I got to go and do a project.

18:54.234 --> 18:55.536
[audio rewinding]
You know,

18:55.536 --> 18:58.105
Lexy can be a real bitch.

18:58.105 --> 18:59.306
I mean‐‐
[audio rewinding]

18:59.306 --> 19:01.642
You know,
Lexy can be a real bitch.

19:01.642 --> 19:02.809
I mean‐‐
‐ Hey.

19:02.809 --> 19:08.215
‐ You know, Lexy can be a‐‐
‐ How's it going in here?

19:08.215 --> 19:10.384
‐ Super.

19:10.384 --> 19:14.388
Thanks for knocking,
by the way. ‐ Devon, tone.

19:14.388 --> 19:17.157
‐ Tone?
What about privacy?

19:17.157 --> 19:19.359
‐ I didn't know
you had anything to hide.

19:19.359 --> 19:25.499
‐ Of course not, Detective.
‐ My roof, my rules. ‐ Copy that.

19:25.499 --> 19:32.372
‐ I need to talk to you
about Jake.

19:32.372 --> 19:34.541
‐ What about Jake?

19:34.541 --> 19:39.479
‐ I think it's best if you
stay away from him from now on.

19:39.479 --> 19:41.748
‐ Mom, I told you,
I barely know him.

19:41.748 --> 19:43.417
And what,
you're picking my friends now?

19:43.417 --> 19:46.086
‐ No, of course not.

19:46.086 --> 19:49.389
But I think I have to draw
the line at certain people.

19:49.389 --> 19:51.158
‐ Certain people?

19:51.158 --> 19:53.193
That's crazy.
What did he do?

19:53.193 --> 19:56.363
‐ Well, for one, people seem
to drop dead around him.

19:56.363 --> 19:59.333
‐ Jake's dad died and now
you're making Jake the bad guy?

19:59.333 --> 20:03.270
‐ This isn't about Jake's dad.
This is about my son.

20:03.270 --> 20:08.375
‐ Yeah, this feels very caring.

20:08.375 --> 20:12.045
‐ Either Jake is trouble,
or trouble seems to follow him,

20:12.045 --> 20:13.347
and I don't want you
mixed up in it.

20:13.347 --> 20:18.118
‐ You're wrong, okay?
Jake wouldn't hurt anyone.

20:18.118 --> 20:19.586
And I'm going to prove it.
‐ You know what?

20:19.586 --> 20:22.523
This isn't a debate.
It's an edict.

20:22.523 --> 20:24.691
Stay away from him.

20:24.691 --> 20:27.594
[somber music]

20:27.628 --> 20:34.535
♪ ♪

20:43.310 --> 20:46.046
