20:48.315 --> 20:50.617
[audio rewinding]
‐ No, she was just mess‐‐

20:50.651 --> 20:53.620
[dramatic, eerie music]

20:53.654 --> 21:00.427
♪ ♪

21:09.303 --> 21:11.605
[knocking on door]

21:22.416 --> 21:24.518
‐ Why are you here?

21:24.518 --> 21:27.521
‐ I just‐‐
I thought it was cool of you

21:27.521 --> 21:33.627
to apologize the way you did.
‐ I know. ‐ I‐‐and I just

21:33.627 --> 21:39.199
thought that you should
have Chucky.

21:39.199 --> 21:45.038
‐ Chucky?
Chucky! ‐ She can have him?

21:45.038 --> 21:52.312
Really? ‐ Yeah.

21:52.312 --> 21:56.083
‐ [squealing]

21:56.083 --> 22:01.088
‐ This means a lot to her.
Thank you.

22:01.088 --> 22:03.590
But just to be clear,
I don't want you to think

22:03.590 --> 22:06.226
we're, like,
friends or something now.

22:06.226 --> 22:12.032
‐ No, no.
No. ‐ Come on.

22:17.104 --> 22:21.108
‐ When it all comes together,
it's like fireworks.

22:21.108 --> 22:22.075
‐ Not friends.

22:22.075 --> 22:26.346
‐ And, God, I love
to watch the sparks fly.

22:26.346 --> 22:29.316
[playful spooky music]

22:29.349 --> 22:35.722
♪ ♪

22:42.429 --> 22:45.732
[ominous music] ♪ ♪

22:45.732 --> 22:48.202
‐ Here you go, Chucky.

22:48.202 --> 22:49.670
‐ Mom, have you seen
my biology book?

22:49.670 --> 22:52.406
‐ Uh‐‐
[shushes]

22:52.406 --> 22:54.541
‐ Great, what's
the little genius doing now?

22:54.541 --> 22:56.710
‐ Shh, look.

22:56.710 --> 22:59.146
[eerie music]

22:59.146 --> 23:01.448
‐ [child's voice]
I like to be hugged.

23:01.448 --> 23:08.222
♪ ♪

23:16.263 --> 23:21.268
‐ Can I give Chucky a hug?
‐ He likes to be hugged.

23:21.268 --> 23:28.675
‐ Okay.
Okay, come here.

23:28.675 --> 23:31.111
[chuckles]

23:33.247 --> 23:34.615
[sighs]
Thank you, Chucky.

23:34.615 --> 23:40.654
That was a good hug.

23:40.654 --> 23:46.527
‐ [indistinct whispering]
‐ He wants to give you a hug.

23:46.527 --> 23:53.133
♪ ♪

23:53.133 --> 24:00.140
‐ Lexy, he's waiting.

24:04.111 --> 24:07.447
[tender, eerie music]

24:07.481 --> 24:09.550
♪ ♪

24:09.550 --> 24:12.686
‐ I like to be hugged.

24:12.686 --> 24:15.255
♪ ♪

24:15.255 --> 24:17.791
‐ Every killer needs a cover.

24:17.791 --> 24:24.531
Personally, I like hiding
behind an innocent face.

24:24.531 --> 24:26.533
‐ Hackensack continues
its streak

24:26.533 --> 24:29.670
as one of the top ten
safest cities in America.

24:29.670 --> 24:32.206
Mayor Michelle Cross cited
a high priority

24:32.206 --> 24:34.708
on safety
and citizen involvement.

24:34.708 --> 24:39.646
‐ Okay, brat, you gonna be okay
in here for a while? ‐ Mm‐hmm.

24:39.646 --> 24:41.648
‐ I thought you were
watching "Westworld."

24:41.648 --> 24:47.254
‐ Chucky says life's too short.
He wants to watch the news.

24:47.254 --> 24:49.223
[TV drones in background]

24:49.256 --> 24:52.192
[ominous music]

24:52.226 --> 24:59.299
♪ ♪

25:00.334 --> 25:03.437
[suspenseful music]

25:03.470 --> 25:08.408
♪ ♪

25:08.408 --> 25:15.516
‐ [growls]

25:15.516 --> 25:17.384
‐ Hey.
Sorry.

25:17.384 --> 25:19.286
It took forever
for my parents to leave.

25:19.286 --> 25:21.255
‐ How long will
they be gone for?

25:21.255 --> 25:22.523
‐ Oh, as long as it takes
for everyone

25:22.523 --> 25:25.359
to finish crying
over poor Jake Wheeler.

25:25.359 --> 25:27.794
‐ I brought your favorite.
‐ Ooh.

25:27.794 --> 25:31.665
‐ Courtesy
of my parents' stash. ‐ Ooh!

25:31.665 --> 25:33.333
Thanks.

25:33.333 --> 25:34.768
[sultry rock music]

25:34.768 --> 25:38.605
‐ Let it go, Junior.
He isn't worth it, all right?

25:38.605 --> 25:45.245
She isn't either.

25:45.245 --> 25:47.247
‐ Why didn't you ask me
to bring something?

25:47.247 --> 25:48.315
‐ [laughing]
Oh, my God.

25:48.315 --> 25:49.816
You're kidding, right?

25:49.816 --> 25:52.719
If your dad caught you stealing
his liquor, he'd be pissed.

25:52.719 --> 25:59.526
Oliver's parents
don't give a shit. ‐ Never mind.

25:59.526 --> 26:03.130
What are you doing
with Jake's doll?

26:03.130 --> 26:06.400
‐ He brought him over
for Caroline.

26:06.400 --> 26:09.036
Oh, and I talked to him
like you wanted me to,

26:09.036 --> 26:10.537
so you can stop giving me shit.

26:10.537 --> 26:13.640
‐ Thanks, Lex.
I appreciate that.

26:13.640 --> 26:18.478
‐ Caroline,
come get your stupid doll.

26:18.478 --> 26:21.381
‐ There you are!

26:21.381 --> 26:24.084
‐ You won't mention that Junior
and our friends came over

26:24.084 --> 26:26.420
to Mom and Dad, right?

26:26.420 --> 26:27.721
It'll be our little secret,
okay?

26:27.721 --> 26:32.759
Cross your heart.
‐ Cross my heart.

26:32.759 --> 26:36.029
[eerie music]

26:36.029 --> 26:39.500
‐ [sighs]

26:39.500 --> 26:46.406
♪ ♪

26:46.406 --> 26:51.178
‐ Thank you for caring enough
about our daughter

26:51.178 --> 26:52.779
to meet with us, but...
[scoffs]

26:52.779 --> 26:56.383
I just need to ask.
How long is this going to take?

26:56.383 --> 26:58.552
Oh, we have theater tickets,
and, you know,

26:58.552 --> 27:01.188
