when the mayor shows up late.

27:01.188 --> 27:05.492
‐ [chuckles] ‐ Hi, hi.

27:05.492 --> 27:09.129
Sorry I'm so late.
Traffic was just terrible.

27:09.129 --> 27:11.598
Hi, Michelle. Hi, Nathan.
Hello, ladies.

27:11.598 --> 27:13.133
‐ Hi.
‐ Mrs. Wheeler.

27:13.133 --> 27:15.469
‐ Hi.
‐ Thank you for joining us.

27:15.469 --> 27:18.172
Okay, so now that
we're all together, uh,

27:18.172 --> 27:19.773
Ms. Fairchild and I would like
to discuss with you

27:19.773 --> 27:24.244
recent events
with Jake and Lexy.

27:24.244 --> 27:27.181
We want to ensure
that each student feels safe

27:27.181 --> 27:28.482
here at Perry Middle School‐‐

27:28.482 --> 27:30.651
‐ And I assure you,
we want that too.

27:30.651 --> 27:33.253
One of my first moves as mayor
was allocating funds

27:33.253 --> 27:35.522
to school safety programs.

27:35.522 --> 27:39.359
‐ We believe that bullying
is unacceptable. ‐ As do we.

27:39.359 --> 27:40.394
‐ It's come to our attention

27:40.394 --> 27:46.366
that Lexy has been
bullying Jake.

27:46.366 --> 27:48.302
[both laugh]

27:48.302 --> 27:50.270
‐ Our daughter
is not the bully.

27:50.270 --> 27:52.239
If anything, she's the victim.

27:52.239 --> 27:53.807
Did you see what that kid did
at the talent show?

27:53.807 --> 27:55.542
He humiliated her.

27:55.542 --> 27:57.578
‐ This has gone far beyond
typical name‐calling.

27:57.578 --> 27:59.479
‐ Look, excuse me,

27:59.479 --> 28:01.381
Jake's been through
a lot lately.

28:01.381 --> 28:03.550
‐ That is not an excuse
for his behavior.

28:03.550 --> 28:06.053
‐ I'd actually like
to bring this back to Lexy.

28:06.053 --> 28:07.521
‐ We don't need to sit here
and listen

28:07.521 --> 28:09.289
